Will this ever be a controlled vocabulary?
To be proposed to EUVocabularies for publication.
To be checked in eInvoicing the relation to VAT code. Awaiting a new change request on other types of TAX.

To be moved into `ePO/item` with a small diagram.
Manufacturer role to be implemented. Manufacturer as a role that is played by an agent and an Item has a manutacturer.

In this diagram the cardinalities have not been modified. This is work in progress. Check the cardinalities in ePOv2.0.1.; e.g. cardinalities between Contract and Period, as well as all attributes of all classes.

properties.documentation:
A document containing a catalogue.
Additional Information: A complete catalogue is provided in such a document.

documentation.value:
A short text by which a thing is known or referred to.
WG Approval 16/11/2021

properties.documentation:
A part of the catalogue.
Additional Information: The catalogue fragment generally represents a difference between two catalogue versions, but there may be other use cases.

A document containing only a fragment of a catalogue expected to alter an existing complete catalogue evolving it to its subsequent version.
Additional Information: One or more catalogue fragments can be provided in such a document. Each fragment has its own update/alteration action.

documentation.value:
The version of the catalogue to be updated.
Additional Information: For example, if we start with source version 005 and add a fragment to it we will end up with a target version number 006.

The version of the catalogue after the update is applied.
Additional Information: For example, if we start with source version 005 and add a fragment to it we will end up with a target version number 006.

properties.documentation:
Proof that compliance to a given standard has been verified.
Additional Information: Such standards may relate to social, ethical and quality etc.

A tax, fee or duty imposed on the item.
Additional Information: Charge category indicates the nature of the tax/duty/fee, for example VAT, CAR, etc. Charge category modifier may be used in case different levels, exemptions or other modifications apply. The charge can be fixed or relative to the price.

Combination of two items where the former enhances the latter.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

Combination of two items which mutually enhance one another.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

Inclusion of an Item into in the described Item.
Additional Information: The item is provided with its components, however, the component items may also be provided separately. For example, a bicycle has wheels as components, but they may be provided as spare parts as well. This relation is useful to describe different package levels of an item or hierarchies of items.
WG Approval: 19/05/2022

Connection between two items.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

documentation.value: The number or the fraction of a related item.

properties.documentation:
Supplantment, displacement or suspension of an Item by the described Item.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

Necessity of an item by the described item.
Additional Information: The described item is provided without other items that are required for proper functionality.
For example, a printer cannot be used without ink cartridge; or a Server cannot be used without its installation.
WG Approval: 19/05/2022
Amount of money required or given in exchange for items.

Name given by an organisation to its product or service, or range of products or services.
Additional information: Brand name allows economic operators to distinctively describe an item in their eCatalogue. This may be different from the "item name".
WG acceptance 10/03/2022

documentation.value:
A short text by which a thing is known or referred to.
WG Approval 16/11/2021

properties.documentation:
A specific design or version of a product or service.
Additional information: This class is meant as a reusable reference to the model name rather than as a set of specifications of an item of this particular model.
WG acceptance 10/03/2022

documentation.value:
A short text by which a thing is known or referred to.
WG Approval 16/11/2021

properties.documentation:
Document providing information about an Item.
WG approval 07/04/2022
The producer of goods or provider of services.

A role of an agent compiling and supplying a catalogue.
Additional Information
The catalogue provider role is usually played by the agent that acts as a seller, or by another agent that acts on behalf of the seller.
WG Approval 28/01/2021

A role of an agent processing a catalogue.
Additional Information The catalogue receiver may not only receive it but also validate it, process it, etc.
The catalogue receiver role is usually played by the agent that acts as a buyer, or by another agent that acts on behalf of the buyer.
WG Approval 28/01/2021
A describing a set of items offered for purchase that can be processed in an electronic way.

documentation.value:
Information about payment conditions applied to all items in the catalogue.
Additional information: This property may need to be used together with the payment arrangements provided in the ContractTerms, where such terms exists.
WG approval 30/06/2022

properties.documentation:
Aggregated information about the terms and specifications for procuring an item.
Details about an item, like prices, packaging, discounts, special promotions, etc.
TC 440:
Detailed information of an item, price and its composition in a Catalogue.
Composition: e.g. information referring to its description, how to order it, what it is made of, properties, delivery conditions, etc.

documentation.value: Indicator, if the item is orderable or not, e.g. because it is temporarily out of stock.
The factor by which the Item net price of an unit of an item can be converted to the orderable unit.
Orderable quantity increment: The increment of Orderable units that can be ordered.
Warranty information that applies to the catalogue line item.
Indicator if the item is offered in accordance to an existing contract.
Textual description of the specific transaction conditions (purchasing, sales, payment) for an item.

properties.documentation:
A production lot in which the item instances were produced.
WG Acceptance 10/03/2022

documentation.value:
The day until which the quality of the item will remain optimal.
WG approval 10/03/2021

The last day until which the item can be used.
WG approval 10/03/2021

properties.documentation:
A product, work, service or any combination of them.
Additional Information: An item can be an atomic thing or a composition of things that together are seen as a unit, e.g. a tetrabrik of milk or an indivisible package of six tetrabriks.
No distinction is provided between services, goods and works to leave room for innovation.
WG approval 30/06/2022

documentation.value:
Explanatory text about the instance of the concept.
WG Approval 30/09/2019
Textual description of the item's dimensions.
URI reference to external item information or specifications, e.g. web address.
Specification of the hazardous nature of an item according to a classification schema. Provides detail of the classification and nature of a hazardous item.
Percentage of value-added tax of the item.
Indicator whether an item is in the supplier's stock. If not in stock the supplier has to order the item.

List of words (e.g, synonyms) to make the item searchable.
WG Approval 7/04/2022

A short text by which a thing is known or referred to.
WG Approval 16/11/2021

properties.documentation: * environmental/ecological/green, * quality, * social, etc.
Additional Information: https://service.unece.org/trade/untdid/d00a/tred/tred5153.htm
Additional Information: https://service.unece.org/trade/untdid/d97a/uncl/uncl5305.htm

This is a controlled list indicating whether an item is a product or service.
Additional information: For example possible values could be: * SER - Trade item is a service * MTO - Trade item is manufactured after order * VQ - Trade item is variable measure item, that is, the quantity in the package is not fixed, and the price for the item varies with the quantity * RC - Trade item is a returnable unit
For example the list of possible item types is available here: https://www.gs1.org/sites/default/files/docs/eancom/ean02s4/part3/dc245.htm
This reference stands for a context dependent controlled list: CPV, UNSPC,
Waiting for code list.
Waiting for code list.
Waiting for code list.

documentation.value: Relation indicating
Code that defines how the line should be applied to an existing eCatalogue.
The label type such environmental, quality, social etc.
Agent issuing the label.
The minimum quantity of the item that can be ordered to the given net monetary value.
The expected amount of time between the order and delivery of an item.
The period of time when the Item can be ordered to the given price.
The price amount of an Item exclusive of taxes and after substracting price discounts.
The quantity at which the net monetary value applies.

The factor by which the base unit of the price can be converted to orderable unit.
Additional information: This is needed when the base price is provided different than the orderable unit. For example, when selling paper, the price may be set per page, but the orderable unit is a package of 500 pieces. Therefore the price needs to be converted to the orderable unit.
Location delivery area where the Item can be ordered to the given price.

The item price based on a standardised unit.
Additional Information: The unit must be indicated in the Quantity, with a quantity value of 1.
The manufacturer's identifier for the item.
The product maker or service provider.

A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019
Coded description of the specific transaction conditions (purchasing, sales, payment) for an item.
The unit in which the item described in this catalogue line can be ordered.
The minimum quantity of an item that is guaranteed by the seller to be delivered.
The maximum number of orderable units that can be ordered according to details provided in the catalogue line, such as price.

A unique identifier of the instance of the concept.
Additional Information
For example, in the case of the Procurement Identifier, this could be the European Public Procurement Identifier, and/or any other identifier provided by the buyer, the service provider or any other stakeholder.
WG Approval 12/11/2019

The source country of the product or service.
Additional Information:
The country of origin can be provided by the buyer as a requirement or by the tenderer information of the item to be provided.
WG Approval 07/01/2020

A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.
Additional Information: In the eCatalogue context, when this relation is used between two items, the resource in the definition refers to Items, i.e. one Item requires another Item.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

The identifier for the instance of the concept based on a standard scheme.
Additional information: For example the GTIN scheme (Global Trade Item Number).
WG Approval 24/02/2022
The net quantity of the item that is contained in each consumable unit, excluding any packaging materials.

A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.
Additional Information: In the eCatalogue context, when this relation is used between two items, the resource in the definition refers to Items, i.e. one item is part of another item.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

An additional item that can enhance the original item.
WG Approval: 19/05/2022

An item that can be added to another item to enhance it.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022

A classification of this item according to a specific system for classifying products or services.
Additional information: Examples of classification schemes are: CPV, UNSPC, eCl@ss, GPC, ...
WG acceptance 10/03/2022

The identifier for the instance of the concept as defined in the catalogue.
WG Approval 24/02/2022
Specification of the hazardous nature of an item according to the UNDG classification schema. Provides detail of the classification and nature of a hazardous item.

An item that if used with another item provides mutual enhancements to both of them.
Additional information: For example, gin and tonic; or smart-phone and smart-watch.
WG Approval: 19/05/2022
A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.

A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.
Additional Information: WG Approval: 19/05/2022

A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.
Additional Information: In the eCatalogue context, when this relation is used between two items, the resource in the definition refers to Items, i.e. one item replaces another item.
WG Approval: 30/06/2022
Value-added tax category of the item.

The identifier for the instance of the concept as defined by the manufacturer.
WG Approval 24/02/2022

properties.name: item labels
properties.documentation: A reference to where the label specification can be found, e.g. a URI.
